@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Blog Post - Bloomfiy";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}

<section class="post-header">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Spring Flower Care Guide</h1>
        <div class="post-meta">
            <span>March 15, 2024</span> •
            <span>5 min read</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="post-content">
    <div class="container">
        <img src="~/Images/blog/spring-care-large.jpg" alt="Spring Flower Care" class="post-image">

        <div class="post-body">
            <p>Spring is a time of renewal and beauty, and what better way to celebrate than with fresh, vibrant flowers? Here are simple tips to help your spring blooms stay fresh and beautiful longer.</p>

            <h2>Watering Tips</h2>
            <p>Most spring flowers prefer consistently moist soil. Water them early in the morning to prevent evaporation.</p>

            <h2>Temperature Matters</h2>
            <p>Keep your flowers in a cool environment away from direct sunlight and heating vents.</p>

            <h2>Simple Maintenance</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Remove wilted flowers promptly</li>
                <li>Change water every 2-3 days</li>
                <li>Trim stems at an angle</li>
                <li>Keep away from fruits</li>
            </ul>

            <p>With these simple tips, your spring flowers will bring joy to your home for much longer!</p>
        </div>

        <div class="post-navigation">
            <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "Blog")" class="back-to-blog">← Back to Blog</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>